                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/116: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany (<persName type="from"
                        >Gordon</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-26T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 26, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 26—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. My 47, March 25, 3 p.m. I spoke with several chiefs of mission last night who
                    took occasion to express their opinion that outside intercession under the
                    present circumstances would be very unwise.</p>
                <p>Jewish owned <hi rend="italic">Berliner Tageblatt</hi> has lined up with <hi
                        rend="italic">Frankfurter Zeitung</hi> in attitude reported in my telegram
                    under reference.</p>
                <p>Probably needless to say but I trust the allusion in yesterday’s telegram to
                    forthcoming interview of leading industrialist with Hitler will be treated in
                    the strictest confidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
